
# Python CLI TODO App

A small, well-documented Python command-line TODO application ready to publish on GitHub.

---- Add, list, complete, and remove TODO items.
- Stores data in a local JSON file (`~/.todo_cli.json`).
- Small and easy-to-read codebase with tests.

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+

## Quickstart


## Project structure

```
todo-cli/
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
├── .gitignore
├── pyproject.toml
├── todo/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── cli.py
│   └── store.py
├── tests/
│   └── test_store.py
└── .github/
    └── ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md
```

---

## README.md (English)

````markdown
# TODO CLI

A tiny, dependency-free command-line TODO application in Python. Perfect as a GitHub project template for beginners.

## Features


1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/todo-cli.git
cd todo-cli
````

2. Install (optional):

```bash
python -m pip install --user .
```

3. Use the CLI:

```bash
# add an item
python -m todo.cli add "Buy milk"

# list items
python -m todo.cli list

# mark item 1 as done
python -m todo.cli done 1

# remove item 1
python -m todo.cli remove 1
```

## Tests

Run tests with pytest:

```bash
python -m pip install --user pytest
pytest -q
```
